benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/tags - Add tags to payment

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04 cover successful tag creation with valid inputs and empty/normal payloads.
Edge/Validation: Scenarios TC05, TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11 cover various invalid inputs, missing headers, malformed bodies, duplicates, extra fields, and invalid UUID formats.

Authorization/Security: TC15 covers unauthorized access, TC16 covers malicious payloads, TC17 covers partial inputs, TC19/TC20 address concurrency and idempotency implications, and TC02 TC03 include optional headers for auditing.
Not Found/Bad Resource: TC05 (non-existent payment) and TC18 (database empty) test 404 scenarios for missing data.
Performance/Load: TC12 (performance under load) and TC20 (concurrency) test timing and stability expectations.
Server Error Handling: TC13 exercises service unavailability with 503 responses.
Boundary/Edge Case: TC14 tests very large payloads; TC04 tests empty array; TC11 tests duplicates; TC18 tests non-existent payments.
gaps: Pagination: No pagination tests are applicable for POST /tags, so not required here.
Caching: No tests addressing caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) for POST responses.
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No explicit tests for rate limiting or throuhghput under burst conditions beyond TC12 concurrency, but not explicit throttling behavior.
Detailed error body schemas: While many error messages are asserted, some tests only check presence of error message; finer-grained schema validation could be richer.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for rate limiting/throttling behavior under high request volume (beyond TC12).
Add tests verifying caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on POST responses if applicable, to ensure proper caching strategy.
Enhance error payload schema validation to assert exact error structure (code, message, details) across more scenarios.
Consider dedicated tests for idempotent re-submission with different concurrent patterns to further confirm no duplicates across edge race conditions.
